Univariate Analysis

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, borrower employment status and borrower credit history. Income range, employment status and amount of credit relation are main interest. Monthly payment amount and borrowers interest rate relaated variables. I have created month, quarter, and year variables from date related variables. I have orderd income range variables from low to high and didnt take into account NA values.

Bivariate Analysis

Amount of monly payment increasies proportionally as Loan amount increasies.
Loan duration decreasies with monthly income increases until it reaches 10000 than dependence dissapiars. High loan amounts have estimated loss less than 0.1. The most delay of payments is observed for incomes less than 10000. LoanOriginalAmount vs MonthlyLoanPayment and OnTimeProsperPayments vs TotalProsperPayments have strongest dependence.

Distribution of loan original amount in USD.
The loan amount is distributed in range of (1000, 35000), the mean value is ~10000 but distribution is negatively skewed and most of loans are <5000. There are spikes at multiplicated numbers of 5000 until the max value.

Plot Two

Description Two

The means of loan amount in USD vs estimated loss.
The plot describes relation between loan amount and estimated loss. Its clearly seen that estimated loss is less than 0.1 for loans with high amount, also in case of estimated loss more than 0.1 mean loan amount is less than 5000$.

Plot Three

Description Three

Monthly income vs loan original amount in years and month.
Loan amount increases in 2013 and 2014 with monthly income >8000. Clearly seen that this began in april 2013 and lasts in first quarter of 2014. We have only first quarter information of 2014. Also in 2007 and 2008 (espacially in April, May) the number of lones in range (15000\(, 25000\)) is incrased for people with income less than 5000$.

Reflection

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, borrower employment status and borrower credit history. Analysed income range, employment status and amount of credit relation are main interest. Also delay of paiment, monthly payment amount and borrowers interest rate relaated variables. Manly dependences between variables are observed for loans less than 10000$.
Loan amount increasies in 2013 and 2014 with monthly income >8000. Clearely seen that this begin in April 2013 and lasts in first quarter of 2014. We have only first quarter information of 2014. Loan Amount mean is more depend on EstimatedLoss than EstimatedReturn. Manly loss<0.1 is preferable for high amount of loans. Return manly vaies from 0 to 0.2. High rate of delays are observed in July 2007 with loan origination grater than 50 with employment status other and income range $2500-49999.

Using full Loan data can be identified problematic customers also with picture of how is changing employment status and income or loan amount, could be used to describe global economic patterns.
